' Target-only architecture: Tool Manager and Skill Manager own configuration parsing, manifests, permission, content loading, and execution.
' Observed behavior: Context already separates tools from the system prompt, but AgentTool combines model metadata and local execution.
' Java divergence: RuntimeToolCatalog and ToolCallDispatcher do not exist in the current pi-mono-java baseline.
' Design reason: send schemas through model tools and forward tool calls without mapping every tool to a Java execution type.
@startuml external_tool_manager_architecture
!theme plain
left to right direction
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #3D8DFF
skinparam packageBorderColor #B8BCC4
skinparam packageBackgroundColor white
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #B8BCC4
skinparam rectangleBackgroundColor #F2F2F2

package "Agent control plane" {
  rectangle "Agent Config vN" as Config
  rectangle "Runtime Assembler" as Assembler
  rectangle "Prompt Compiler" as Prompt
  rectangle "Model Manager" as ModelManager
}

package "Independent manager plane" {
  rectangle "Tool Manager\nparse toolsets and permission\nresolve and invoke" as ToolManager
  rectangle "Skill Manager\nresolve versions\nactivate instructions" as SkillManager
  rectangle "Tool Manifest\nmodel descriptors + opaque bindings" as ToolManifest
  rectangle "Skill Manifest\nprompt descriptors + opaque bindings" as SkillManifest
}

package "pi-mono-java runtime" {
  rectangle "ResolvedAgentRuntime\nimmutable and versioned" as Runtime
  rectangle "RuntimeToolCatalog\nmodel-visible descriptors" as ToolCatalog
  rectangle "ToolCallDispatcher\ndirect forwarding" as Dispatcher
  rectangle "Managed Skill Adapter" as SkillAdapter
  rectangle "AgentSession + Agent" as Session
  rectangle "AgentLoop" as Loop
  rectangle "Provider Adapter" as ProviderAdapter
  rectangle "ManagerBackedAgentTool\ncompatibility only" as CompatAdapter
}

Config --> Assembler
Assembler --> ToolManager: raw tools config
Assembler --> SkillManager: raw skill refs
Assembler --> ModelManager: model refs
Assembler --> Prompt: structured system
ToolManager --> ToolManifest
SkillManager --> SkillManifest
ToolManifest --> Assembler: model descriptors
SkillManifest --> Assembler: prompt descriptors
Prompt --> Assembler: compiled system
Assembler --> Runtime
Runtime --> ToolCatalog: bind pinned descriptors
Runtime --> Dispatcher: bind manifest
Runtime --> SkillAdapter: create per session
ToolCatalog --> Session: model tools
Dispatcher --> Session: execution entry
SkillAdapter --> Session
Session --> Loop
Loop --> ProviderAdapter: system, messages, tools
ProviderAdapter --> Loop: tool call
Loop --> Dispatcher: name and arguments
Dispatcher --> ToolManager: invoke opaque binding
Loop --> SkillAdapter: activate skill
SkillAdapter --> SkillManager: activate opaque binding
Runtime ..> CompatAdapter: optional transition
CompatAdapter ..> ToolManager: invoke opaque binding
@enduml

